Good choice for lunch whether you want an entree or a sandwich.  The chicken sandwich with bacon and melted cheese with sweet potato fries was really good and reasonably priced at $12.  Conveniently located next to the Farragut West metro and a short walk to the Renwick and White House.

Unfortunately one of the people dining with us had an awful experience. They asked for their fish not to have sauce on it - first came out exactly as another at our table with sauce. Sent it back and came out with no seasoning and in the same sauce. Maybe wouldn't have been so bad had the salad he ordered with dressing on the side not come out with dressing on it and had to get that corrected. They did comp the meal so at least they tried to make up for mistakes. The rest of us had good food.

A disgrace to our nations’s capital city.  We waited 20 minutes before even being offered menus, our inattentive waiter Oscar had to be asked for water which took another 5 minutes. After 40 minutes of being ignored, we asked to speak with the manager who informed us our food was behind 25 other orders despite there being only a handful of other people present.  If this is how this restaurant operates, then they won’t last long.

Charming bistro off the lobby of my hotel.  Scallops, salads & tapenade were quite tasty.  Stay away from the onion tart as the kitchen hasn't mastered puff pastry tart shells - soggy, soggy, soggy!  Also, the unmelted cheese scattered over top of the nicely melted cheese was a mis step.
Very beautiful, food delicius

I went to this place for lunch during a three week business trip in DC. The wait time was reasonable and the food was fresh. We were served with hot french bread while awaiting our meal. The served food was good quality and the waiter friendly. Prices are reasonable by the quality.
Great place to hang out
Gotta love a lamb burger for lunch

This place was a cool oasis after walking in the hot sun of a 100° DC July afternoon.  I had a burger and my partner had a beet salad.  Both were very tasty and the service was good.  Price with tip was approx $60.

Great happy hour place.   Their house wines are really good, the happy hour menu is pretty large with lots of choices,  and the wait staff is super friendly.   In the summer, the staff opens up the entire front wall so it is just like eating outside without all the pesky bugs.

This restaurant is a hidden gem. The food was delicious. We were on a walking tour around the city and very hungry. We stopped there without prior planning and as we were taking a look at what the outdoor posted menu offered, two extremely satisfied tourists went out and randomly strongly encouraged us to try it as they were very happy with their own experience. They talked non stop about how good the food was and how it should be an absolute loss if we dont give it a try. This is when another tourist got out of the restaurant and acertained what was previously advised. We did not regret it at all. The menu is rich and limited at the same time which is something I appreciate especially when I am new to the experience as I get easily lost when it comes to choosing from a big unfamiliar list. Each one of us had a preference and we all shared to taste. Everything was delicious ( crab cake, crab and avocado stack, soup of the day, filet mignon, LAMB BURGER, lobster raviolli). Also the music was perfect. Calm french ambiance. They also serve bread and unsalted butter while the order is being processed. The service is a little bit slow though but the waiters are helpful.
Great drinks

I had lunch here with a colleague. It was great. The wait time was reasonable and the food was fresh. We were served with hot french bread while awaiting our meal. It's just around the corner from the White House.

This is an adequate bar and restaurant. They have good happy hour specials on food and drink, but only Peroni on draft and a pretty limited bottled beer selection. I just wish they would broaden their offerings a bit more.

Theq sauce for the calamari was different.  So price wise , things were better then expected.  The waiter was nice to give me more hot tea and bags.  Helps dropping a few "L" "B" 's. This was the worst dining experience I have had in a very long time. We had a table of about 14 but were the only ones in the restaurant. Prices weren't cheap and my steak was very over cooked, as was my friend's burger. The server never came back to ask us how things were. It took over an hour to give us our checks. Still we were the only ones in the restaurant. It was like a very strange dream. Then they added 20 percent gratuity on top of the tax, which is normally what I would tip, but not after an experience like this??!! I said something but left it as is, but the experience was so bad that I felt like I had to leave a review. Never again would I even humor coming back. I'd rather go hungry.

A cosy little restaurant selling american food that wants to be french. Food is pretty yum. Price is okay. Has good opening hours.if  you're worried about value, the burgers are pretty reasonable and the sweet potato fries are tasty. I ordered the lambshank which was fall off the bone delicious. Went there for breakfast as well had some pretty yummy eggs and delicious french toast (seriously good!) Slow service. We stood awkwardly waiting at the door for a few minuets until they felt included to seat us in their near empty dining room. The server was not clear on where to sit so we seated ourselves. I also had to get up to grab our menus. All this I could have delt with.  The part I’m most unhappy about was the hair INSIDE my (way over cooked) poached egg. My father, who I had taken out for breakfast, had to flag our server down. He removed the plate and offered me something else, but did not apologize. The cook gave me a dirty look from the kitchen. They did not charge me and I just opted for a ginger ale.  Dad said his food was alright, But my ginger ale was served room temperature.  I will not be returning nor will I recommend this establishment.

**As an amendment to my earlier review, as we contacted the manager of the restaurant as soon as I noticed the errant charge.  The manager looked into the issue, and he called my husband back with his sincere apologies and refunded not only the tip amount, but the amount for our entire check.  I am pleasantly surprised at the outcome; I feel that the manager did everything in his power to completely rectify the experience we had, and I appreciate that.  Honestly, too, I think the food would have been delicious, had it been served immediately, so it may be worth a try if you are in the area. My original review is still below, because, while the manager rectified the situation, it still important for other's to know things like this, especially when spending the kind of money this place calls for, and to know if you get service like this, get a manager involved before you leave. ______________________________________________________________________  This place was awful.  After we placed our order, we never saw the server.  Our food was served to us cold, after sitting in the window for who knows how long, and it took me another ten minutes to flag a server down to address the issue, and instead of fixing the issue, they put my medium rare steak in the microwave and brought it back out to me.  Again, after this, I never saw a server again.  It took us twenty minutes of servers walking by us and our plates sitting on the edge of the table, doing their side work, to get them to take our plates and bring the check.  My husband and I left no tip, after spending $80 on an awful, re-heated meal.  However, when I looked at my bank account this morning, the server took it upon himself to charge a $14 un-authorized tip to my card.  So if you do go here, make sure you keep your receipt, and check the charge a few days later.  This was the worst restaurant experience I've ever had.
